--- !u!114 &1008417464
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1008417461}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: dbefc55dcf6fd4242a5ebcd31ba89c98, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  finalQuestions:
  - questionInfo: 'A 25-year-old man involved in purchasing drugs was knifed in the
      abdomen in the left upper quadrant. On examination in the emergency department,
      it was difficult to determine whether the knife had penetrated into the peritoneal
      cavity. It was decided to do a midline peritoneal lavage below the umbilicus
      to see if there was any free blood in the peritoneal cavity. The following
      layers of tissue were penetrated by the trocar and cannula to enter the peritoneal
      cavity except which? '
    questionChoices:
    - Fatty and membranous layers of superficial fascia
    - Rectus sheath and rectus abdominis muscle
    - Fascia transversalis
    - Extraperitoneal tissue and parietal peritoneum
    correctChoice: Rectus sheath and rectus abdominis muscle
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: The following statements concerning the right lung are true except
      which?
    questionChoices:
    - It possesses a horizontal and an oblique fissure.
    - Its covering of visceral pleura is sensitive to pain and temperature.
    - The lymph from the substance of the lung reaches the hilum by the superficial
      and deep lymphatic plexuses.
    - The bronchial veins drain into the azygos and hemiazygos veins
    correctChoice: Its covering of visceral pleura is sensitive to pain and temperature.
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'The absence of a body makes the ___ vertebra atypical: '
    questionChoices:
    - 1st cervical
    - 2nd cervical
    - 3rd thoracic
    - 4th thoracic
    correctChoice: 1st cervical
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'A 55-year-old woman has severe aortic incompetence, with the blood
      returning to the cavity of the left ventricle during ventricular diastole.
      To hear the aortic valve with the least interference from the other heart sounds,
      the best place to place your stethoscope on the chest wall is :'
    questionChoices:
    - the right half of the lower end of the body of the sternum.
    - the medial end of the second right intercostal space.
    - the medial end of the second left intercostal space.
    - the fifth left intercostal space 3.5 in. (9 cm) from the midline.
    correctChoice: the medial end of the second right intercostal space.
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'The orbicularis oculi muscle is innervated by the:'
    questionChoices:
    - facial nerve
    - lacrimal nerve
    - maxillary nerve
    - nasociliary nerve
    correctChoice: facial nerve
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which of the following muscles partially inserts on the articular
      disc of the temporomandibular joint?
    questionChoices:
    - Medial pterygoid
    - Anterior fibers of the temporalis
    - Posterior fibers of the temporalis
    - Lateral pterygoid
    correctChoice: Lateral pterygoid
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'The neck is divided into anterior and posterior triangles using
      ____ muscle as land mark: '
    questionChoices:
    - 'Anterior belly of digastric '
    - Sternocleidomastoid
    - 'Scalenus anterior '
    - Sternohyoid
    correctChoice: Sternocleidomastoid
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'The superior orbital fissure is a gap within the ___ bone: '
    questionChoices:
    - Frontal
    - Parietal
    - Sphenoid
    - Temporal
    correctChoice: Sphenoid
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'In a gouty patient on allopurinol treatment who develops a malignancy,
      the administration of the following anticancer drug could result in more side
      effects because of reduced metabolism:'
    questionChoices:
    - Cytarabine
    - Methotrexate
    - 6- Mercaptopurine
    - 5-Fluorouracil
    correctChoice: 6- Mercaptopurine
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: "When an individual is standing, the base of the lung relative
      to the apex of the lung has a: Greater (\u2191), smaller (\u2193), Equal (\u2194)"
    questionChoices:
    - A
    - B
    - C
    - D
    correctChoice: B
    questionImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 55c3070a5d61d6e49bd0bd761cc9eb14, type: 3}
  - questionInfo: 'A 32-year-old patient diagnosed with chronic inflammatory bowel
      disease, ulcerative colitis type, which of the following features is most likely
      an associated condition:'
    questionChoices:
    - Noncaseating granulomas on microscopic examination.
    - Primary sclerosing cholangitis.
    - Transmural colonic inflammation.
    - Intestinal strictures.
    correctChoice: Primary sclerosing cholangitis.
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A 65 year old gentleman who smoked at least one pack of cigarettes
      per day for the past 25 years presented with progressive breathing difficulty.
      His pulmonary function test results showed marked airway obstruction. Which
      of the following respiratory tract structures in the lungs is likely to be
      affected initially and mostly by the underlying disease?
    questionChoices:
    - Alveolar duct and sac
    - Terminal bronchioles
    - Respiratory bronchioles
    - Pulmonary capillaries
    correctChoice: Respiratory bronchioles
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which lymphoma that tends to cause significant facial disfigurement?
    questionChoices:
    - Hodgkin lymphoma
    - Diffuse large B-cell lymphoma
    - Mantle cell lymphoma
    - Burkitt lymphoma
    correctChoice: Burkitt lymphoma
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'The ___ artery exits the middle cranial fossa through the optic
      canal:'
    questionChoices:
    - Buccal
    - Pterygoid
    - Masseteric
    - Ophthalmic
    correctChoice: Ophthalmic
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which bacterial structure is inhibited by vancomycin?
    questionChoices:
    - Cell membrane
    - Ribosomes
    - Cell wall (peptidoglycan layer)
    - Flagella
    correctChoice: Cell wall (peptidoglycan layer)
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which selective differential solid culture media is used to diagnose
      cholera?
    questionChoices:
    - MacConkey agar
    - Blood agar
    - 'Thiosulfate Citrate Bile Salts Sucrose (TCBS) agar '
    - Chocolate agar
    correctChoice: 'Thiosulfate Citrate Bile Salts Sucrose (TCBS) agar '
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which of the following childhood exanthems should be treated with
      antibiotics?
    questionChoices:
    - 'Measles '
    - Chickenpox
    - Scarlet fever
    - Fifth disease
    correctChoice: Scarlet fever
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which organism causes Beaver fever?
    questionChoices:
    - Giardia
    - Salmonella
    - 'E. coli '
    - Cryptosporidium
    correctChoice: Giardia
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which of the following viruses threatened the Panama canal-building
      effort?
    questionChoices:
    - Zika virus
    - Dengue virus
    - Yellow fever virus
    - Chikungunya virus
    correctChoice: Yellow fever virus
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which of the following bacterial pathogens is commonly associated
      with hyponatremia in pneumonia cases?
    questionChoices:
    - Streptococcus pneumoniae
    - Legionella pneumophila
    - Haemophilus influenzae
    - Mycoplasma pneumoniae
    correctChoice: Legionella pneumophila
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which cytokine would result in the production of a dimeric antibody
      during immunoglobulin isotype switching?
    questionChoices:
    - Interleukin-4
    - Interleukin-2
    - Transforming growth factor beta
    - Interferon-gamma
    correctChoice: Interleukin-4
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: "ATP hydrolysis reaction is given as: (ATP \u2192 ADP + Pi). According
      to the following table, the cell with highest yield of energy from ATP hydrolysis
      is:"
    questionChoices:
    - A
    - B
    - C
    - D
    correctChoice: D
    questionImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 561d79f122b87594d8d26f56dfc64a05, type: 3}
  - questionInfo: With respect to the value of delta G given for each reaction. Which
      reaction is the fastest?
    questionChoices:
    - Reactions 1 and 2 are about the same speed
    - Reaction 4 is the fastest
    - Reactions 3 and 4 are about the same speed
    - I cannot tell
    correctChoice: I cannot tell
    questionImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: d1f3ae62bef23c84985136a5fc714605, type: 3}
  quizUIobj: {fileID: 609381636}
  timerObj: {fileID: 1981497918}
